<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,754,961]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,754,780]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,761,778]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,754,780]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[393,516,755,780]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,516,755,780]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished by a head with anteriorly extended, prominent stylate eyes, head width wider than mesonotum, pronotum shorter than mesonotum, and timbal covers not being concave dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
